<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.179217>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Keilbachia ancylonema sp. n. (E holotype, A, B, C, D paratype, F from Myanmar). A: Maxillary palpus, dorsal view. B: Antennal flagellomere 4, ventral view. C: Apical part of tibia 1, prolateral view. D: Part of hypopygium, ventral view. E, F: Gonostylus, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/179217/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.179220>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Keilbachia mirabilis sp. n. (B, C, E, F holotype, A, D paratypes). A: Maxillary palpus, dorsal view. B: Antennal flagellomere 4, ventral view. C: Apical part of tibia 1, prolateral view. D: Wing, dorsal view. E: Part of hypopygium, ventral view. F: Gonostylus, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm, for D 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/179220/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

